Adjust racks to middle and upper positions and preheat #oven{} to 450 degrees. Wash and
dry all produce. Cut @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges, like steak
fries. Halve @Carrot{8%ounce} lengthwise.

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @Vegetable Oil{2%teaspoon},
half the @Autumn Spice Blend{1%tablespoon}, @Salt{}, and @Pepper{}. Toss carrots on a
second baking sheet with a large drizzle of @Vegetable Oil{3%teaspoon}, salt, and
pepper. Roast potatoes on upper rack and carrots on middle rack until tender, about
~{30%minutes} for potatoes and ~{20-25%minutes} for carrots.

Meanwhile, pat @Pork Chops{12%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with
salt and pepper. Heat a drizzle of oil in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add pork
and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{4-5%minutes} per side. Turn off heat;
remove from pan and set aside.

Meanwhile, halve, core, and dice @Apple{1}. Halve, peel, and dice @Yellow Onion{1}.
Finely chop @Parsley{1/4%ounce}.

Melt @Butter{1%tablespoon} in pan used for pork over medium heat. Add onion and cook
until softened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Add apple and @Dried Cranberries{1%ounce} and cook,
stirring, until slightly softened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Stir in @Chicken Stock Concentrate{1},
@Cinnamon{1%teaspoon}, and @Water{1/3%cup}. Simmer, stirring, until apple is tender
and mixture has a thick, saucy consistency, about ~{4%minutes}. (TIP: If mixture seems
dry, stir in another splash of water.) Season with salt and pepper.

Stir any resting juices from pork into apple mixture. Divide pork, carrots, and
potatoes between plates. Top pork with apple mixture. Sprinkle everything with
parsley and serve.